  <title>Using X# in Visual Studio</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Using X# in Visual Studio</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">XSharp comes with 2 options for development environments:</para>
    <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal">Chris Pyrgas has adjusted his existing IDE to support XSharp (it is now called XIDE, and compiled in XSharp !)</li>
      <li styleclass="Normal">We supply Visual Studio integration for Visual Studio 2015. If you do not have Visual Studio 2015, you can download a (<text style="font-weight:bold;">free!) </text><text style="font-weight:normal;">community edition from Visual Studio from the web:</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="weblink" href="https://www.visualstudio.com/en-us/downloads/download-visual-studio-vs.aspx" target="_blank" style="font-weight:normal;">https://www.visualstudio.com/en-us/downloads/download-visual-studio-vs.aspx</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">The Visual Studio integration is also work in progress. What is supported in this version is:</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Edit</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Compile</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Debug</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Source control</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Windows Forms Editor</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">WPF Editor</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Resource editor (no code generation yet)</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Settings editor (no code generation yet)</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Known issues:</text></para>
    <list id="2" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Most of the intellisense options in the Editor are not working </text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">There are no editors for VO Binary entities yet</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:normal;">There is no support .designer.prg yet</text></li>
    </list>
  </body>
</topic>
